latestIgtvVideos.title: EASIEST (& effective) Home Workout 🔥
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Ignore my laughter I was just being awks recording this😛 No equipment needed! First set is cardio peak (not shown here) either jumping jacks, high knees, skips- your call. 
1. Any Cardio Peak (1 minute)
2. Jumping Pulse Squat x 20
3. Knee Push ups x 20
4. Glute Kick Back x 15 (per side)
5. Side Plank (or normal plank) 
Just repeat this circuit 5 times for beginners 💪🏼 Shoutout to @muscle.asylum.in for giving me the kick to workout #NoMoreExcuses

latestPosts.caption:
Meet Sahiba Bali, Global Governance Initiative's 30 under 30 global achiever, 2023.

As part of the marketing category, Sahiba Bali has unleashed the power of persuasion and creativity- blending the arts and sciences of marketing.

Sahiba Bali wears many hats- she is not only an actor having worked with Imtiaz Ali in movies or with shows on Netflix and Sony Liv but also a marketeer having led marketing projects at Zomato for 4 years and then as Associate Director at an ed-tech firm. 

Moreover, she is a content creator who loves travelling, food and wellness. 

This mindset, together with her persistence in achieving her goals was the key to bringing her the success she is enjoying today. She is one of the most trending Indian woman on YouTube currently. 

Before all this, she graduated in Economics from Delhi University and went to Business School for post-grad in the UK, and later Oxford University.

Join us in celebrating Sahiba and the other inspiring individuals who have made it onto Global Governance Initiative's 30 under 30 international list. 

For the coming days, we will be sharing the power stories of our under 30 awardees. So you may follow this space for more. 

Let us take inspiration from young success stories of our 30 under 30 and inspire global youth to do better for our world.
